OL,3,CWhy the Tories may struggle to fund
OL,4,Cthe tax cuts they've pledged
OL,6,F"Vote Tory, pay less tax." That's the
OL,7,Fpitch.JThe manifesto sets out cuts
OL,8,Fworth #17.2 billion a year by the end
OL,9,Fof the next parliament.JIf re-elected,
OL,10,Fthe Tories say they would cut the rate
OL,11,Fof National Insurance to 6% by April
OL,12,F2027 for employees.JAnd phase-out the
OL,13,Ftax altogether for the self-employed,
OL,14,Fover a five year period.JThe Institute
OL,15,Ffor Fiscal Studies (IFS) calculates
OL,16,Fsomeone on average earnings of #35,000
OL,17,Fa year would pay #300 less if the full
OL,18,Fcut was introduced.JThe saving is not
OL,19,Fhigher because the Tories would
OL,20,Fcontinue to freeze the thresholds of
OL,21,Fnational insurance and income tax for
OL,22,Fseveral years until 2028.JAs for the
OL,23,Ftax burden, this cut would be a drop
OL,24,Fin the fiscal bucket. The overall tax
OL,25,Ftake would continue rising north of
OL,26,F#1100 billion.
