OL,3,CWhy the Tories may struggle to fund
OL,4,Cthe tax cuts they've pledged
OL,6,FTax as share of GDP is currently
OL,7,Fforecast to reach 37.1% in by 2028/29
OL,8,F- the highest level for 80 years.JThe
OL,9,FTory manifesto pledges would bring
OL,10,Fthat down to 36.5% - still the highest
OL,11,Flevel for, erm, 80 years.JIn addition
OL,12,Fto tax cuts, the Tories promise a big
OL,13,Fincrease in defence spending.JThe
OL,14,Fmanifesto says these would be funded
OL,15,Fby cuts to welfare spending, a
OL,16,Fcrackdown on tax avoidance, layoffs in
OL,17,Fthe civil services and "quango
OL,18,Fefficiences" - whatever they might be.
OL,19,FSceptical? You're not alone.JTake
OL,20,Fwelfare. Spending shot up in the last
OL,21,Fparliament.JThe number of people
OL,22,Fgetting one health-related benefit has
OL,23,Fsoared from 3.2 million to 4.2 million
OL,24,Fsince the pandemic and is forecast to
OL,25,Fcontinue rising.
