OL,3,CWhy the Tories may struggle to fund
OL,4,Cthe tax cuts they've pledged
OL,6,FThe Tories say they will save #12
OL,7,Fbillion a year by holding financial
OL,8,Fsupport at current levels.JThat would
OL,9,Fbe a challenge. New claims for
OL,10,Fdisability support are coming through
OL,11,Fat a rate of 40,000 a month.J"We've
OL,12,Fhad a doubling in the numbers applying
OL,13,Ffor disability benefits," says Paul
OL,14,FJohnson of the IFS. "It's entirely
OL,15,Freasonable for a government to think
OL,16,Fabout how to tackle that. But can they
OL,17,Fget #12 billion? You can see why they
OL,18,Fwould want to but not how."JThe risk
OL,19,Fhere is the Tories get elected, don't
OL,20,Fget the savings they want and have to
OL,21,Fborrow to fund tax cuts and extra
OL,22,Fdefence spending.JAnd it's not clear
OL,23,Fthey would be able to do this because
OL,24,Fthe Tory manifesto also contains a
OL,25,Fpledge to get debt falling as a share
OL,26,Fof national income over a five year
